registry/ideas.jsonl:46:{"schema": "kot-idea/1", "id": "idea-compositional-rollup-invented-concepts", "title": "Encoder/decoder static-analysis roll-up of sentence structure into invented composite concepts (maintainer-proposed; Fable to design)", "idea": "The encoder does static/symbolic analysis to ROLL UP recognisable compositional structure ('a is b', 'a AND b', 'a OR c') into a single INVENTED composite concept whose vector is DETERMINISTICALLY derived from its parts, so those tokens reach the LLM as one concept; the decoder carries a per-utterance dictionary of the invented concepts to expand them losslessly when it must state them.", "slots": [{"architecture": "encoder", "part": "composition-rollup", "role": "compress"}, {"architecture": "decoder", "part": "invented-concept-dictionary", "role": "expand"}, {"architecture": "model", "part": "io", "role": "cheapen"}], "mechanism": "The kernel already binds clauses via exact Hadamard TPR + HRR convolution, so a composite like 'a AND b' HAS a deterministically-derivable vector from its parts. Apply that binding at ENCODE time to collapse recognised connective/copula structures (AND/OR/is-a) into fewer concept tokens; pass a per-utterance invented-concept dictionary to the decoder for lossless expansion. Family: deterministic structured-data->concept parsing + symbolic composition between layers.", "epistemic": "EXTRAPOLATION", "epistemic_refs": ["maintainer-proposal:2026-07-09", "doc:reports/lit-structured-parsing-and-inner-symbolic.md", "encoder:construction-B binding algebra (Hadamard TPR + HRR)"], "compatibility": {"alternative_to": [], "orthogonal_to": ["idea-crosslingual-phrase-coverage-io-compression"], "requires": ["idea-a2-adapter-injection"], "conflicts_with": [], "conflicts_note": "MUST respect idea-ast-input-injection-boundary (X1): injecting structure the LLM can already read is PARITY on ACCURACY and static-analysis does not transfer in. So this idea is justified ONLY on the COMPRESSION/EFFICIENCY endpoint (fewer tokens, like idea-code-input-canonicaliser survives on VARIANCE) \u2014 never as an accuracy-from-structure claim."}, "dependencies": ["idea-a2-adapter-injection", "idea-code-input-canonicaliser"], "open_questions": ["Which compositional patterns are safely + deterministically roll-uppable (AND/OR/is-a/copula) without meaning loss?", "Does the composite vector (from the existing binding algebra) actually carry the meaning into the LLM through the trained bridge (Law 1)?", "Lossless decode via the invented-concept dictionary \u2014 round-trip fidelity.", "How much real text is captured by these patterns (coverage -> achievable compression ratio)?", "Net effect on model accuracy at matched budget vs the kernel-as-text null."], "feasibility": {"cost_tier": 2, "readiness": "blocked", "blocked_on": ["fable-design", "maintainer-signoff"]}, "decisiveness": 3, "uncertainty": 4, "leverage": 3, "source": "maintainer", "ladder_ref": "in-tokenisation-normalisation", "candidate_ref": null, "status": "proposed", "assumption_refs": [], "premise_eligible": false, "notes": "Maintainer (Jesse) 2026-07-09, framed as SEPARATE from kernel design (an encoder/decoder architecture). DO NOT BUILD YET \u2014 Fable designs + signs off. Honesty linkage: constrained by idea-ast-input-injection-boundary (X1) \u2014 frame as compression/efficiency, NOT accuracy-from-structure. Reuses the existing deterministic binding algebra for composite vectors."}
