registry/ideas.jsonl:51:{"schema": "kot-idea/1", "id": "idea-leaderboard-benchmark-eval", "title": "Leaderboard-benchmark evaluation of kernel AUGMENTATION on the checkable slice, coverage-gated \u2014 SCOPED as N1-LB (architecture-ladder \u00a710): b-cov census (Tier 0, now) + LB-1 covered-slice eval (Tier 1-2, LB-GATE)", "idea": "Measure 'how good the best kernel support actually is' on LLM-leaderboard benchmarks as an AUGMENTATION value-add on the kernel-CHECKABLE subset of each benchmark at matched compute, plus a per-benchmark checkable-slice-growth trajectory across kernel versions \u2014 never a naive blended 'kernel vs leaderboard' score. Two artefacts: (1) b-cov, a deterministic Tier-0 benchmark-checkability census (m0b's sibling; per-benchmark lemma-touch sieve + mode-indexed kernel_checkable fractions \u03ba_B^verify / \u03ba_B^engine, keyed to kernel/world-layer/mapper/grammar hashes, appended per kernel version); (2) LB-1, an f2b-TRANSFER-shaped covered-slice eval on named public benchmarks, gated by LB-GATE.", "slots": [{"architecture": "model", "part": "evaluation", "role": "measure"}], "mechanism": "b-cov census: per pinned benchmark, compute the d-ext R-C lemma-touch sieve and the runtime verifier's own kernel_checkable predicate (plus the L3 mapper+closed-grammar parse fraction) without any model call; log the trajectory per kernel version. LB-1: on the census-checkable slice only, arms {model-alone; kernel-verify-retry (only if f2b-TRANSFER PASSes); shuffled-kernel-verify; kernel-as-text; gloss-self-verify} at matched budget, R1+R3 minimum, full F0 metric vector V with the cost_ratio efficiency headline; later modes (L1a canonicalisation, L3b routed-hybrid, grounding-lint) join only after their own rung PASSes. Reporting: coverage-first, blended \u0394_B = \u03ba_B \u00d7 \u0394_covered stated as a derived identity (off-slice is byte-identical by construction), selection-effect disclosure (model-alone acc checkable vs non-checkable), NICHE-SCOPE banner below thresholds.", "epistemic": "EXTRAPOLATION", "epistemic_refs": ["maintainer-proposal:2026-07-09", "measured:f2b-replicate d-ext byte-identical (kernel_checkable=false => 100% abstain; registry/assessments/f2b-replicate.json)", "measured:d-ext lemma-touch 2903/5957 (~49%) vs item-checkability 0/500 (data/d-ext/manifest.json) \u2014 checkability, not vocabulary, is the binding constraint", "measured:m0b coverage 0.3542 @ molecules-v0 (corpus-indexed, TinyStories-validation; extrapolates to no benchmark)", "verdict:l3a (engine-oracle PASS, gold-parse only \u2014 no NL behaviour licensed)", "doc:docs/next/architecture-ladder.md \u00a710 (N1-LB \u2014 the scoped design)"], "compatibility": {"alternative_to": [], "orthogonal_to": ["idea-kernel-precision-linter"], "requires": ["f2b-transfer PASS (for the verify-retry mode's seat; a FAIL re-gates LB-1 on the next passed mode, L3b or L1a)"], "conflicts_with": [], "conflicts_note": "Premature to RUN at current coverage \u2014 already measured, not conjectured: d-ext shows the best supported config is byte-identical to model-alone on a real public benchmark (0/500 checkable), so a naive run measures coverage, not kernel quality, and reads as misleadingly 'bad'. Value theses stay CORRECTNESS + EFFICIENCY on the checkable slice. The b-cov census part is NOT premature: Tier 0, ~$0, now-eligible, and is itself the coverage-growth instrument."}, "dependencies": ["b-cov-census (new Tier-0 instrument, \u00a710.1)", "f2b-transfer", "kernel-variant-expansion", "haiku-tier-mint-pipeline", "structured-db-world-layer-ingestion", "kot-axiom query-grammar growth (FK-L3-3)", "m0b-coverage-instrument"], "open_questions": ["WiC sourcing: pre-declared rank-1 lexical benchmark is unavailable unauthenticated (pilehvar/wic HTTP 401, d-ext preference walk) \u2014 authenticated HF sourcing or original distribution, fail-closed on provenance.", "LB-GATE thresholds (\u03ba_B >= 0.10 headline / 0.20 banner-free; >=500 checkable items on >=2 benchmarks) are STIPULATED design constants mirroring m0b X=20% and f2b powering \u2014 maintainer ratifies or resets at freeze.", "Benchmark contamination in pretraining mixtures: carried as the accepted RT-7a limitation (eval splits first) \u2014 is a stronger decontamination step worth its cost at LB-1 freeze?", "When do L3b (engine answers checkable items directly \u2014 likely efficiency winner on simple-factual slices) and L1a modes join? Own rung gates, never discovered at LB-1.", "Census-vs-runtime predicate drift: LB-1 pre-declares an engagement floor on the census-checkable slice; disagreement is INSTRUMENT-INVALID (fix the census, never reinterpret)."], "feasibility": {"cost_tier": 2, "readiness": "blocked", "blocked_on": ["f2b-transfer PASS", "LB-GATE census yield (>=500 checkable items on each of >=2 external benchmarks)"], "now_eligible_part": "b-cov census: Tier 0, ~$0, CPU, this box \u2014 no gate"}, "decisiveness": 2, "uncertainty": 3, "leverage": 3, "source": "maintainer", "ladder_ref": "N1-LB (docs/next/architecture-ladder.md \u00a710)", "candidate_ref": null, "status": "scoped", "assumption_refs": [], "premise_eligible": false, "notes": "SCOPED by Fable 2026-07-09 (bead kernel-of-truth-ou3): full design + placement in docs/next/architecture-ladder.md \u00a710 (N1-LB). Answers to the stub's open questions: (1) coverage milestone = LB-GATE (\u00a710.4): f2b-TRANSFER PASS + census-measured >=500 checkable items on >=2 benchmarks + \u03ba thresholds 0.10/0.20 + maintainer sign-off; evaluated on b-cov output, never estimated. (2) triage (\u00a710.2, STIPULATED prior, census decides): Tier A = WiC / OpenBookQA / ARC-Easy / CommonsenseQA / TruthfulQA-mc / BoolQ / MMLU definitional-heavy subjects per-subject; Tier C essentially-none = GSM8K/MATH, HellaSwag, WinoGrande, code, broad trivia, multi-hop. (3) modes (\u00a710.3): verify-retry first (only MEASURED mechanism, contingent on f2b-TRANSFER), L3b/L1a/grounding-lint join only after their own rung PASSes; mandatory nulls inherited from f2b (kernel-as-text, gloss-self-verify, shuffled-kernel). (4) reporting (\u00a710.5): coverage-first, blended-score identity \u0394_B = \u03ba_B \u00d7 \u0394_covered descriptive-only, forbidden 'improves <benchmark>' phrasing with a licensed template, selection-effect disclosure, trajectory-is-the-deliverable, NICHE-SCOPE banner. Placement: NOT a ladder rung \u2014 a recurring coverage-gated measurement surface tied to the efficiency track (F0 accounting, cost_ratio headline); b-cov now, LB-1 post-gate, recurs per kernel version. Do NOT run LB-1 at current coverage."}
registry/ideas.jsonl:52:{"schema": "kot-idea/1", "id": "idea-kernel-precision-linter", "title": "Kernel as a grounding/precision guardrail + controlled-language LINTER for LLM output (maintainer-proposed; Fable design complete 2026-07-09, awaiting maintainer sign-off)", "idea": "Use the kernel as, or as part of, a framework that guardrails / 'lints' LLM outputs to follow a very precise linguistic style — producing clear, concise, precisely-articulated written language with no meaningless or hallucinated text — by grounding every proposition in the kernel's controlled, NSM-grounded vocabulary and flagging/quarantining/rewriting what cannot be grounded.", "slots": [{"architecture": "framework", "part": "output-guardrail", "role": "lint"}, {"architecture": "framework", "part": "controlled-language-rewrite", "role": "rewrite"}, {"architecture": "seam", "part": "verifier", "role": "add"}], "mechanism": "DESIGNED (docs/next/kernel-precision-linter.md, node N-PL). Pipeline: segment -> map+extract (mapper a1-hybrid + proposition extractor into kot-ast/1 fragments; EXTRACTION IS THE INSTRUMENT, P10 extraction-failure gate applies) -> classify each proposition into a five-class verdict lattice {G+ grounded-consistent, G- grounded-contradicted (analytic/axiom/record contradiction — the only class the kernel may call WRONG), U ungrounded/coverage-gap (informational by default, NEVER rendered as false), V vacuous (rhetorical filler / post-explication tautology — the 'meaningless text' target, distinct from U), A ambiguous (mapper abstention)} via kernel_checkable + decode-verify + kot-axiom sidecar + world layer (the L3a engine in its third seat: answerer/checker/linter) -> act per declared mode {P permissive flag report; S strict contract: output must be kernel-parseable controlled surface with ungroundable content only inside explicit unverified-quarantine blocks — fail-closed, hallucination-surface reduction STRUCTURAL not detective (the CNL/ACE move); R rewrite: deterministic record->text re-render with mechanical round-trip gate (re-parse recovers identical proposition set)} -> deterministic versioned lint report (same text + same kernel version => byte-identical report). Severity = f(class, mode), never f(groundability) alone — this is the over-flagging defence at low coverage. Rewrite surface (fork LNT-F2 decided as design recommendation): kernel-native Minimal-English-style renderer at molecule-tier vocabulary with expansion-on-demand to primes; pure-prime NSM rejected (verbosity; Minimal English lesson) and ACE rejected as target (two-semantics tax) but kept as literature comparator.", "epistemic": "EXTRAPOLATION", "epistemic_refs": ["maintainer-proposal:2026-07-09", "doc:docs/next/kernel-precision-linter.md (N-PL design, 2026-07-09)", "measured:m0b coverage 0.3542 molecules-v0 / 0.7841 wn31-aligned membership band (registry/verdicts/m0b.json)", "measured:l3a engine exactness 0.9955 / refusal 0.9911 Wilson-LB, formalism-properties envelope (registry/verdicts/l3a.json)", "measured:f2b-replicate d-ext 100% abstention on kernel_checkable=false (the naive-linter degeneracy existence proof)", "lit:Kuhn 2014 CNL survey, Computational Linguistics 40(1) [search-verified 2026-07-09]", "lit:FActScore arXiv:2305.14251 atomic-fact decomposition [search-verified 2026-07-09]", "lit:Minimal English (Goddard ed. 2018) + Riemer 2006 via reports/nsm-and-knowledge-injection.md"], "compatibility": {"alternative_to": [], "orthogonal_to": ["idea-crosslingual-phrase-coverage-io-compression", "idea-compositional-rollup-invented-concepts", "idea-leaderboard-benchmark-eval"], "requires": [], "conflicts_with": [], "conflicts_note": "Orthogonal VALUE THESES to the compression cousins (they=efficiency/I-O compression, this=correctness/precision of surface language) but SHARED COMPONENTS: mapper parse front-end, the kernel-native record->text renderer (their decoder-side expansion and this idea's rewrite are the same artefact), and the haiku-tier coverage-growth dependency. Law-2 discipline: the decisive null is a prompted frontier LLM given the SAME kernel records as text ('lint/rewrite precisely; flag unsupported or vague claims'); the kernel's defensible structural wins are verdict determinism/versioning/auditability and the mode-S fail-closed contract, and per-class flag F1 at matched cost is an open empirical fight it can honestly lose (kill K-P1). ungroundable != false is handled by the lattice + severity policy, not by hope; class-U UI vocabulary is 'unverifiable-here', never 'hallucination' (binding naming decision)."}, "dependencies": ["mapper-a1-hybrid", "encoder-decoder", "kernel_checkable-machinery", "kot-axiom-engine-l3a", "record-renderer-to-build", "haiku-tier-mint-pipeline"], "open_questions": ["LNT-F1 extractor identity for mode P: deterministic-parser-only (abstention-bounded engagement) vs LLM-assisted extraction under a P10-style fidelity gate (re-imports stochasticity ahead of a determinism pitch).", "LNT-E0 census: proposition-level CONJUNCTIVE coverage (all content lemmas + frame) on real LLM outputs — necessarily <= 0.3542 token-mass, possibly single-digit percent; the Stage-2 engagement ceiling, measured not assumed.", "K-P1: do the per-class flags beat the kernel-as-text prompted-LLM null on F1 at matched cost — and if not, does the determinism/audit property premium alone carry deployment value (maintainer judgment)?", "K-R1/K-R2: renderer/parser round-trip >= 0.95 on the covered fragment (mechanical), AND human-rated intent fidelity (Riemer circularity: parse-step meaning loss is invisible to the round-trip by construction).", "K-S1: the mode-S constrained-output tax on task success (constrained-decoding alignment-tax caution; P10 IF-1 format-tax fork) at current coverage.", "K-N1: false-alarm rate on clean human-authored precise text — the linter-noise adoption killer (Bessey 2010 lesson), co-primary in every flag eval."], "feasibility": {"cost_tier": 1, "readiness": "blocked", "blocked_on": ["maintainer-signoff"]}, "decisiveness": 3, "uncertainty": 4, "leverage": 4, "source": "maintainer", "ladder_ref": "L0-verifier-seam / L1a-out (output-side canonicaliser); corrected from the stub's in-tokenisation-normalisation — no in-network rung required, composes with all L1b/L2x", "candidate_ref": null, "status": "proposed", "assumption_refs": [], "premise_eligible": false, "notes": "FABLE DESIGN COMPLETE 2026-07-09 (bead kernel-of-truth-z82; this line supersedes the 2026-07-09 stub per last-line-wins). Full design: docs/next/kernel-precision-linter.md — verdict lattice, three modes (P/S/R), staged usability (Stage 0 Tier-0 kot-lint CLI usable NOW: coverage-independent vacuity/ambiguity flags + wn31-band vocabulary-membership annotation + dogfooding; Stage 1 strict-mode scoped covered domains; Stage 2+ coverage-gated), eval plan LNT-E0..E3 with pre-shaped kills, forks LNT-F1..F4. Coverage-dependence is a staircase not a wall. Shuttle/SHACL-CS synergy = formalism craft + candidate tooling reuse (EBNF-driven generation for the renderer) ONLY; directives-1 boundary: no RDF/SHACL semantics enter the kernel. Honest value-prop read (N-PL section 10): stronger VALUE FRAMING than verifier-offload (aligns with measured kernel strengths + NSM's identity as reductive paraphrase; has a coverage-independent usable core offload never had; HE1 primary FAILED at F2 while the f2b lift remains circularity-untested) but exactly as EXPOSED empirically until LNT-E0/E1 run. Awaiting maintainer sign-off before any candidate promotion; nothing runs, nothing frozen."}
registry/ideas.jsonl:54:{"schema": "kot-idea/1", "id": "idea-compositional-rollup-invented-concepts", "title": "Encoder/decoder static-analysis roll-up of sentence structure into invented composite concepts (maintainer-proposed; Fable design complete 2026-07-09, awaiting maintainer sign-off)", "idea": "The encoder does static/symbolic analysis to ROLL UP recognisable compositional structure ('a is b', 'a AND b', 'a OR c') into a single INVENTED composite concept whose vector is DETERMINISTICALLY derived from its parts, so those tokens reach the LLM as one concept; the decoder carries a per-utterance dictionary of the invented concepts to expand them losslessly when it must state them.", "slots": [{"architecture": "encoder", "part": "composition-rollup", "role": "compress"}, {"architecture": "decoder", "part": "invented-concept-dictionary", "role": "expand"}, {"architecture": "model", "part": "io", "role": "cheapen"}], "mechanism": "DESIGNED (docs/next/io-compression-ideas.md, node N-IOC §3). PATTERN SCOPE grounded in the actual closed grammar (encoder/src/lexicon.ts): 'a AND b' = NATIVE (conjunction is clause sequencing; roll-up = encodeExplication of the multi-clause AST); 'a is b' = NATIVE within the kind/part frames + equative clauses (outside the frames the parser ABSTAINS, never approximates); 'a OR c' = NOT EXPRESSIBLE at v0 — the closed operator inventory {NOT,CAN,MAYBE,IF,BECAUSE,WHEN,LIKE,AFTER,BEFORE,VERY,MORE} has NO OR, and the MAYBE paraphrase is semantically lossy (epistemic possibility != disjunction), so OR is deferred behind a MEASURED need (B-E0 counts the OR-forfeit mass; adding OR = encoder version change + grammar design bar). Free riders: NOT/CAN/MAYBE/IF/BECAUSE/WHEN complexes. Scope rule: roll-up unit = any MAXIMAL PARSEABLE explication fragment, with {is-a, clause-AND, operator-complex} as pre-registered reporting strata. MINTING: composite AST -> canonical JCS -> content-hash URN (design-hash-input.md; identical composites dedupe globally, per-utterance dictionary = novel slice; frequent composites feed idea-A's mint queue) -> construction-B vector (exact Hadamard TPR within clause, whitened unitary HRR across clauses; zero training, byte-deterministic) -> X4 projection -> ONE soft token via the E5/A2 adapter (Law-1 topology). Fork B-F1 bridge identity: (a) zero-shot E5 bridge (trained on single concepts) vs (b) composite-trained bridge on a disjoint composite split (E5 nonce discipline); both arms run. DECODER: dictionary is SYSTEM-SIDE (never in LLM context — binding accounting rule, else savings invert); expansion = exact URN lookup -> canonical AST -> the deterministic record->text renderer (the SAME artefact as N-PL's rewrite mode); NO cosine anywhere (X3-compliant; unbinding decode is diagnostic-only). Round-trip is exact BY CONSTRUCTION at symbol level; guarded by a Tier-0 property suite (bar 100% — a failure is a bug, not a result). X1 FRAMING (binding): justified ONLY on compression/efficiency; primary = tokens/FLOPs/latency, co-primary = accuracy NON-INFERIORITY (TOST); accuracy-superiority claims from structure BANNED at prereg; structure-as-text arm = expected-parity CONTROL. Null family: full text; kernel-as-text; L1b-FLAT per-concept tokens (the decisive INCREMENTAL null — roll-up must beat flat, K-B2); matched-token trained compressor (K-B4, HE3 kill); shuffled-composite (E9-defl; recovery => no kernel credit, K-B3). Cost: zero mint cost (derived, not authored — B's structural advantage over A), ~0 marginal CPU/query, one-time possible composite-bridge training on V; corpus savings = engagement x per-span savings where engagement <= conjunctive coverage (likely well below 0.3542 token-mass) — B-E0's engagement number is the live-or-die number and is free. Evals: B-RT property suite + B-E0 roll-up engagement census (both Tier 0, $0, NOW-eligible; census outputs per-stratum engagement, span-savings distribution, dedupe stats, OR-forfeit count, achievable compression ratio); B-E1 consumption (Tier 2–3, rides F3 cap +$20–60, R1–R2, full arm family x B-F1). Kills: K-B0 engagement < floor (~2% sanity default), K-B1 non-inferiority fails under both bridge arms (Law-1 toll wins), K-B2 <= L1b-flat Pareto, K-B3 shuffled recovery, K-B4 trained-compressor parity.", "epistemic": "EXTRAPOLATION", "epistemic_refs": ["maintainer-proposal:2026-07-09", "doc:docs/next/io-compression-ideas.md (N-IOC design, 2026-07-09)", "encoder:construction-B binding algebra + closed operator inventory (encoder/src/lexicon.ts — the OR-absence finding)", "measured:X0 byte-determinism / X1 adversarial margins / X2 decode 51-54 encoder-side / X4 projection distortion", "measured:E5 single-concept nonce-transfer PASS +28.5pp at R1 (existence proof for ONE pinned token; composites strictly beyond it)", "lit:idea-ast-input-injection-boundary X1 (arXiv:2602.06671 parity + arXiv:2505.12118 no-transfer) — the framing constraint", "doc:reports/lit-structured-parsing-and-inner-symbolic.md", "measured:m0b coverage envelope + d-ext membership!=engagement"], "compatibility": {"alternative_to": [], "orthogonal_to": ["idea-crosslingual-phrase-coverage-io-compression", "idea-kernel-precision-linter"], "requires": ["idea-a2-adapter"], "conflicts_with": [], "conflicts_note": "MUST respect idea-ast-input-injection-boundary (X1): structure injection is accuracy-PARITY and static-analysis does not transfer — so this idea is justified ONLY on the COMPRESSION/EFFICIENCY endpoint (survival-by-endpoint, the idea-code-input-canonicaliser precedent); accuracy is a non-inferiority co-primary, superiority claims banned, structure-as-text runs as expected-parity control. Must beat kernel-as-text (Law 2) AND the L1b-flat incremental null AND the matched-token trained compressor; must survive the trained bridge (Law 1 — E5 proved single concepts only, hence fork B-F1). LCM/CALM: edge instantiation, no exponent claims at v0; escalation inherits the L2c phi discipline."}, "dependencies": ["idea-a2-adapter", "idea-code-input-canonicaliser", "record-renderer-to-build", "mapper-a1-hybrid"], "open_questions": ["B-E0: corpus engagement of maximal parseable fragments per stratum — above or below the K-B0 floor (~2% sanity default, reset at freeze)? and the OR-forfeit count (the measured case for/against the grammar extension).", "B-F1: does the single-concept-trained E5 bridge carry COMPOSITE vectors zero-shot, or does B need (and can it afford) a composite-trained bridge?", "K-B2: does roll-up beat L1b-FLAT per-concept tokens on the compression-accuracy Pareto, or does it merely match it?", "K-B3: does the shuffled-composite control recover accuracy non-inferiority (=> parity is context redundancy, no kernel credit)?", "Dictionary/dedupe dynamics at corpus scale: global invented-concept dictionary growth, and which frequent composites earn promotion to named concepts (feedback into idea A).", "Round-trip suite at bar 100% over generator+mutator strata (implementation guard, not science)."], "feasibility": {"cost_tier": 2, "readiness": "blocked", "blocked_on": ["maintainer-signoff"]}, "decisiveness": 3, "uncertainty": 4, "leverage": 3, "source": "maintainer", "ladder_ref": "in-tokenisation-normalisation", "candidate_ref": null, "status": "proposed", "assumption_refs": [], "premise_eligible": false, "notes": "FABLE DESIGN COMPLETE 2026-07-09 (bead kernel-of-truth-5iu; this line supersedes the 2026-07-09 stub + utq correction per last-line-wins). Full design: docs/next/io-compression-ideas.md §3. Honest headline findings from the design pass: (1) OR is not in the v0 operator inventory — 'a OR c' roll-up is out of scope until a measured B-E0 forfeit count justifies an encoder version change; (2) round-trip losslessness is exact by construction (system-side exact-by-URN dictionary + shared deterministic renderer, X3-compliant), so the science lives in parse ENGAGEMENT (B-E0) and bridge FIDELITY (B-E1/B-F1), not in round-trip; (3) invented concepts cost nothing to mint (deterministic derivation) — B's cost story is structurally cleaner than A's. DO NOT BUILD until maintainer sign-off; then B-RT + B-E0 (Tier 0, $0) run first; B-E1 waits on F3 gates; pre-registered cost/accuracy Pareto metric vector declared via the candidate template before any spend. X1 honesty linkage preserved: frame as compression, NEVER accuracy-from-structure."}
