registry/assumptions.jsonl:7:{"backing_ref": "data/code-v0/README.md; docs/design-a5-code-worldlayer-oracle.md section 2", "claim": "The A5 construct->concept mapping table is a stipulated modelling choice: extracted Python constructs are asserted classes of the minted code-v0 concepts (python-module, python-function, python-class) and edges are asserted under the minted code-v0 relation concepts (code-calls, code-defines, code-imports) plus the REUSED kernel-v0 part-of/has-part pair read as transitive lexical containment. Every mapping is by EXACT minted content-hash URN (X3 trap honoured); the adequacy of these six structural definitions as kernel concepts is stipulated, not evidenced, and the code-v0 records are structural definitions, NOT kot-ast/1 NSM explications.", "date": "2026-07-09", "id": "ASM-0007", "load_bearing": true, "owner": "runner-3", "rationale": "v0 has no code-construct concepts; minting six structural-definition concepts through the canonical mint tool (content-addressed, corpus-specific profile kot-code-construct/1, precedent math-v0/pm-ast/1) lets the code vertical run today with exact concept identity. Revisit condition: when the idea-A sub-programme mints NSM-explicated code concepts, re-author code-axioms-v0/code-world-v0 against them and re-run as a successor id; the stipulation then lapses.", "status": "open", "tag": "STIPULATED"}
