tput_fields resolve, separation+P10 gates PASS, best_k=4, gold-oracle field null, both safety bounds self-terminate.", "run_log": "poc/f2b/opus-runs/20260709T104212Z/run-log.md (full command + stdout trail; Opus-execution practice 1)."}, "executed_by": "opus", "executor_model": "claude-opus-4-8", "experiment": "f2b-replicate", "incident": "Two prior full-phase A10G launches of the pre-right-size design each ran ~3.5 h (too heavy). Correction 1 (seq 1) fixed the instrument defects (per-cell flush + safety bounds) but did NOT change the design magnitude. This correction implements the architecture-advisor RIGHT-SIZED design.", "kill_criterion_status": "kill (a)(b)(c) verbatim UNCHANGED; the gold-oracle diagnostic-ceiling sentence was removed (arm dropped). Separation gate, shuffled kill (>=30% recovered fraction), Holm family and verdict rules unchanged.", "kind": "pre-final-reset-refreeze", "legitimacy": "Lawful pre-registration correction, NOT a post-hoc amendment: f2b-replicate is absent from registry/gng0-signoff.json frozen_records and no results-log/f2b-replicate.jsonl exists (no run record was ever logged). The freeze was reset to DRAFT, right-sized, and re-frozen through prereg-freeze under the standard lints; the frozen record itself states this path.", "refrozen_sha256": "21d401777d2b11bca98b0528a58ebb23e774e4d7e4bee5434a746be76a66771d", "root_cause_check": {"actual_heaviness": "The magnitude was the driver: per_arm_items=1000 x seeds=5 x retry_sweep {1,2,4} (worst-case 2+3+5=10 attempt-passes per retry arm) x the full arm set INCLUDING the gold-oracle-retry arm, x the 500-item external d-ext slice run through every arm's own pipeline. The harness's own --dry-plan estimated ~3.26 h point / ~6.52 h worst on A10G for that design \u2014 the >3.5 h runs were inside plan, just too heavy for routine iteration.", "finding": "NO. Inspected the runner cell driver (poc/f2b/runner/f2b_runner.py run_cells): every retry/verify arm (kernel-verify-retry, shuffled-kernel-verify-retry, gloss-self-verify-retry, and the now-dropped gold-oracle-retry) ran ONLY at R1 (SmolLM2-135M). R3 (SmolLM2-1.7B) was invoked ONLY for the single-pass model-alone baseline (k=0). There was NO 1.7B retry ladder anywhere in the superseded design either \u2014 so R3-retries were not the cause.", "question": "Were the ~3.5 h marathons caused by a 1.7B (R3) retry ladder?"}, "schema_version": "kot-correction/1", "seq": 2, "spend_note": "this correction's validation spent $0 (mock + dry-plan, CPU/local; no GPU, no network billing). The full A100 run is NOT launched by this correction \u2014 it awaits the maintainer Tier-1 go.", "supersedes_frozen_sha256": "a5c8b84bd326c60860ba291ebdd7ba7df9c8c328a29adc2cd10a515fa424005e"}
registry/corrections/f2b-replicate/1-prefreeze-correction.json:1:{"author":"runner-2","authorized_by":"operator directive 2026-07-09 (diagnose the stopped full run, fix, re-freeze); implementation fix only, design unchanged","changes":["poc/f2b/runner/f2b_runner.py (sha e14de1a8... -> af527206c9573c6e7c5dd5380d8123ffbd96c720af13cdd1c5ae2017f3ce0018): (a) gold-oracle-retry acceptance loop explicitly hard-capped at GOLD_ORACLE_MAX_ATTEMPTS=8 (realized cap min(k+1,8)); every gold cell records gold_attempts_cap + the per-item gold_reached_within_cap vector (== item_correct by construction: acceptance is exact-gold, final answer is the last attempt) — the diagnostic 'does the model reach gold within the cap' is preserved with a provably bounded loop; (b) NEW CellGuard safety instrument on EVERY arm: per-cell wall-clock timeout (default 3600 s A10G / 9000 s T4, --cell-timeout-s) plus max-generations-per-item cap (default 16 vs structural max 10, --max-gen-per-item); a breach emits a flushed exit:'timeout' record carrying the breach coordinates (never item_correct — nothing fabricated) and aborts with ERR_CELL_TIMEOUT in bounded time; verdict-gen excludes exit!='ok' records, so a breached run reads as INCOMPLETE-DATA, fail-closed; (c) Emitter now appends+fsyncs each record at emit time and the driver logs one line per cell with elapsed seconds — a stopped run leaves every completed cell on disk and visible in the log stream","poc/f2b/smoke/check_mock.py extended (section 9): asserts all-ok exits on a normal run, the gold cap fields and their construction invariant, and that BOTH safety bounds self-terminate with rc!=0 + ERR_CELL_TIMEOUT + a flushed exit:'timeout' record","pins.harness_manifest dc8ede054783809285d8850c7a0edfe4885cae7d2b2302758823dc2d50014517 -> 186a20f85207cd72f9bef586010dfb28e314a12ed96149cf1298bfd2a3e56f98 (staged-bytes manifest sha, recomputed by poc/modal/modal_f2b.py's own manifest code)","NO design change: arms, seeds, retry sweep, endpoints, separation gate, Holm family, verdict rules and kill text are byte-identical to the superseded freeze; mock item_correct/item_correct_external vectors are value-identical to the pre-correction 01:36 UTC Modal mock run across all 32 cells (verified)"],"date":"2026-07-09T05:26:00Z","diagnosis":["SUSPECT FALSIFIED: gold-oracle-retry was never unbounded — its acceptance loop was structurally capped at k+1 <= 5 attempts (retry_sweep {1,2,4}), and the recovered container log proves every gold cell completed: '[f2b 9796.9s] cells gold-oracle-retry k=4 done'. Every other retry/generation loop was likewise bounded (verify/self-verify: k+1; PRM: best-of-2; alone/text: 1).","THE RUN WAS PROGRESSING, NOT HUNG: last recovered log line '[f2b 11126.6s] cells gloss-self-verify-retry k=1 done' (3.09 h in); the stop came ~25 min later, mid gloss-k=2, with ~1.5-2 h of work remaining. The harness's own --dry-plan estimates 3.26 h point / 6.52 h worst-case on A10G; a >3.5 h run was inside plan. The 'leaner than F2' expectation ignored the doubled item count (1000 fresh + 500 external through each arm's own pipeline), the added full-cost shuffled arm, and 5 seeds.","THE ACTUAL DEFECTS (what made a healthy run indistinguishable from a hang, and what could have made a real hang silent): (1) all run records were buffered in memory and written only at process end, so 3.5 h of completed cells left ZERO bytes in the results channel; (2) progress logs were per-arm-x-k (one line after all 5 seeds), leaving silent windows of 20+ min; (3) NO per-cell wall-clock timeout and NO max-generations-per-item cap existed on any arm, so a genuinely pathological cell WOULD have burned the full 12 h Modal timeout with nothing shipped. The staged runner bytes that ran are byte-identical to the audited local file (sha e14de1a8a77cfb88da223d576f45b3448a5fc949debe79fdca095a36bf2994c2, confirmed against the 01:36 mock-run provenance)."],"evidence":{"dry_plan":"A10G point estimate 3.26 h / worst case 6.52 h / $3.59-$7.18 (unchanged by this correction)","log_note":"modal app logs retention returned only the tail; earlier lines expired. The 01:36 UTC mock-run provenance (poc/f2b/results-incoming/20260709-013627-modal/) pins the staged bytes.","modal_app":"ap-Nt5nAOeTxjXpwRYa6V6CqF (kot-f2b, created 2026-07-09 01:37 UTC, user-stopped)","recovered_log_tail":["[f2b  9796.9s] cells gold-oracle-retry k=4 done","[f2b  9917.6s] cell kernel-as-text done","[f2b 11126.6s] cells gloss-self-verify-retry k=1 done","Stopping app - user stopped from CLI."]},"experiment":"f2b-replicate","incident":"The first full-phase launch (Modal app ap-Nt5nAOeTxjXpwRYa6V6CqF, A10G, started 2026-07-09 01:37 UTC) was operator-stopped after ~3.5 h with an empty results channel. Suspected cause at stop time: an unbounded gold-oracle-retry loop.","kill_criterion_status":"kill criterion verbatim text UNCHANGED","kind":"pre-final-reset-refreeze","legitimacy":"Lawful pre-registration correction, NOT a post-hoc amendment: at correction time f2b-replicate was not GNG-0-signed (absent from registry/gng0-signoff.json frozen_records) and no results-log/f2b-replicate.jsonl exists — the stopped run shipped no run records and none were logged, so the P-9 cutoff (first final-phase run record) was not crossed. The freeze was reset to DRAFT, corrected, and re-frozen through prereg-freeze under the standard lints. The frozen record itself states this path: 'ANY staged-byte change after freeze requires a correction record before any final-phase run.'","refrozen_sha256":"a5c8b84bd326c60860ba291ebdd7ba7df9c8c328a29adc2cd10a515fa424005e","schema_version":"kot-correction/1","seq":1,"spend_note":"stopped full run consumed ~3.5 GPU-hours A10G (~$4 at list) against usd_cap $60; no measurement was produced or discarded (the run shipped no records); this correction's validation spent $0 (mock, CPU)","supersedes_frozen_sha256":"2a2ab93b4910a328df364d100924fc63e38853623b7f9e97da7c071bf9dabccb"}
