d_rag; per-cell stratum tables, latency/FLOPs ratios, truncation counts, trivial-baseline brackets and direct-arm covered-exact are DESCRIPTIVE (never Holm, never verdict-bearing)","n_control":122,"n_covered":855,"n_queries_per_cell":977,"pilot_rule":"any pre-freeze prompt/extraction iteration runs ONLY against a 30-query synthetic toy-world probe set (urn:kotw:v0:code-fn-toy--*, disjoint from the corpus by construction); a5-eval items are never seen before the frozen run (FK-A5L-1 is decided there)","power":"decidability: engine conjunctive point ~0.996 (fresh-measured; a5-consistent); at n=977 paired queries the BCa CI half-width is <~0.03 for any plausible LLM accuracy, so LB>0.10 vs UB<=0.10 is decidable across the plausible range; planning value best-LLM conj 0.45-0.75 => power ~1; design remains decision-valid up to best-LLM conj ~0.85","retrieval_rule":"all code-world-v0 records whose subject or object URN string-equals any entity URN in the query (instance-of: entity + concept); EXACT string match only (X3-compliant, no similarity step anywhere); + the 5 code-axioms-v0 records rendered verbatim in every rag prompt; empty retrieval renders a pinned no-records line; build-time completeness lint requires the expected answer's supporting records to be a subset of the retrieved set for every covered query (violations => instrument-invalid; FK-A5L-2 closure-walk fallback resolves pre-freeze)","sap_prng_seed":20260709,"scoring_asymmetry_disclosure":"engine scored STRICT (a5 rules unchanged: provenance+license+exact ERR codes); LLM scored LENIENT (normalised set/boolean match, any-refusal on controls, no provenance) — every asymmetry pro-LLM, making engine superiority conservative; 6/122 out-of-scope-concept controls are refusal-expected for all arms (disclosed; 0.6 percent weight)","seed_note":"greedy decode is deterministic given the pins; seed 0 is the registered placeholder (a5 convention)","successors":"a5-llm-frontier (frontier/long-context + source-in-context