ement block is itself a gate failure. Rejection rate 0 is the F2/d-ext vacuity signature (verify == alone byte-identical); rate ~1 with no acceptance is the never-accepts degeneracy — neither may ever read as a hypothesis outcome","eval_floor":200,"fresh_items":"data/d-qa-t: 360 kernel-covered, kernel_checkable=true items over the 108 covered concepts, generator seed dqat/1|f2b-transfer|20260710 (pre-committed verbatim in prereg_doc §3.1), ID namespace dqat:, leak rule LC8-t fail-closed (full-prompt-surface disjointness from ALL 650 d-qa items AND all 1000 d-qa-r items; reference corpora byte-pinned inside the builder, DQAT_ERR_REFPIN on drift); built by data/d-qa-t/build-dqat.py — same four item templates, same canonical-record rendering and fail-closed leak machinery as the committed data/d-qa-r/build-dqar.py, with a RE-AUTHORED availability-aware per-concept plan sized to exactly 360 (per concept: def-match + term-match + TRUE-preferring claim; plus a 36-concept fourth-item claim subset prioritising concepts with fresh claim segments remaining — claim-true supply is bounded by prior d-qa/d-qa-r surface consumption at 57 fresh segments over 43 concepts, MEASURED; LC7 enforces yes/no <= 0.75 fail-closed; NO LLM item authorship; prereg_doc §3.1 records why no seed-and-count change of build-dqar.py can reach 360). EVAL SET = the first 250 externally-labelled items in pinned rank order (deterministic prefix; floor 200, below which the runner refuses)","headroom_gate":"acc_ext(R1-alone, 3-seed mean) <= 0.85 else INSTRUMENT-INVALID: a saturated baseline cannot measure a lift and must not read as NULL or FAIL","holm_family":"ONE family F-secondary(f2b-t), membership pre-declared: beats_gloss_self_verify, shuffled_low_recovery (recovery ub95 < 0.30 on the external-gold lift), plus — conditional on the separation gate — noninferiority_vs_r3 (external-gold acc of the verify arm non-inferior to 1.7B-alone at margin 0). Reported-only, never Holm, never verdict-bearing: external endorsement A with CI, dual-scoring contrast lift_mem - lift_ext with CI, transfer_ratio, seed-sign (3/3), cost_ratio_vs_R3","iface_gate":"P10 unchanged from f2b-replicate: >= 300 labelled outputs at the verifier host rung (R1), re-verified mechanically from the pinned d-xif labelled set through THIS harness's extraction machinery; extraction-failure Wilson-LB > 10% => INSTRUMENT-INVALID (instrument events, never hypothesis events)","n_generated":360,"per_arm_items":250,"power":"advisor/P8 carry-over from the f2b-replicate right-size: n=250 items x 3 paired seeds gives ~0.92 one-sided power at absolute Delta=0.10 for the paired primary; the fixed pre-registered k=4 removes retry-budget selection from the bootstrap entirely (no sweep, no in-resample selection); stage-1 endorsement gate powered at n_planned=360 (Wilson LB at expected 0.85 is 0.816 > 0.70 bar)","retry_sweep":[4],"sap_prng_seed":20260710,"separation_gate":"instrument gate on EXTERNAL gold, pre-declared, gating ONLY the noninferiority_vs_r3 Holm member: acc_ext(R3-alone) - acc_ext(R1-alone) >= 0.05 (3-seed mean) AND one-sided 95% BCa lower bound > 0; on failure that secondary leaves the Holm family BEFORE any p-value comparison (the gate is a deterministic function of the alone arms only); the absolute primary always reads","stage_discipline":"STAGE 1 BEFORE ANY GPU: build d-qa-t -> freeze -> adjudicate -> pin d-adj-t (ops amendment fills the declared placeholder) -> append the adjudication-instrument final-phase record -> verdict-gen; FAIL (kill d) stops the experiment at ~$0 GPU; INCOMPLETE-DATA (stage-1 passed, fields for later rules unset — fail closed) is the lawful intermediate state licensing stage 2; then reuse-check + dry-plan + mock before the single-GPU final run"},"scale_rungs":["R1","R3"],"seeds":[0,1,2]},"efficiency_relevant":true,"endpoints":[{"id":"primary","metric":"/analysis/effect_size","role":"primary","smallest_effect_of_interest":{"type":"cohens_h_vs_R1_alone_external_gold","value":0.2},"test":"ABSOLUTE superiority on EXTERNALLY-ADJUDICATED gold (no denominator, margin 0): effect_size = acc_ext(135M + kernel-verify-retry, the single pre-registered retry budget k=4) - acc_ext(135M-alone); paired item BCa bootstrap (B=10000, PRNG seed 20260710), one-sided alpha=0.05; reject iff the one-sided 95% BCa lower bound > 0. Accuracies are seed-averaged per-item means on the 250-item externally-labelled d-qa-t eval set (P8 §1.2/§1.7 discipline). This is the ground-truth-independence primary: gold here is fixed by blind judges, never by the kernel's string-equality"},{"id":"sec-endorsement","metric":"/analysis/external_endorsement","role":"secondary","test":"STAGE-1 endorsement statistic (measured rate, reported with Wilson bound; the kill-d trigger): A = share of resolved blind adjudications whose external gold equals membership gold (concordant cannot-say = disagreement); FAIL (kill d) fires iff one-sided 95% Wilson LB < 0.70 — evaluable before any GPU spend","wilson_gate":{"expected_rate":0.85,"n_planned":360,"threshold":0.7}},{"id":"sec-adjudication-gate","metric":"/gates/adjudication_valid","role":"secondary","test":"G-adj INSTRUMENT gate (not a hypothesis test): n_adjudicated >= 300 AND unresolved-disagreement <= 15% AND raw two-judge agreement >= 0.80; failure => INSTRUMENT-INVALID (judge-quality events never read as evidence about the kernel)","wilson_gate":{"expected_rate":0.92,"n_planned":360,"threshold":0.8}},{"id":"sec-engagement-gate","metric":"/gates/engagement_valid","role":"secondary","test":"RT-7a engagement INSTRUMENT gate: over kernel-verify-retry cells, decidable_fraction >= 0.95 AND attempt-0 rejection rate in [0.05, 0.95] AND >= 1 final answer differing from attempt 0; missing engagement block => gate failure; failure => INSTRUMENT-INVALID (the F2/d-ext vacuity signature can never again read as a hypothesis outcome)","wilson_gate":{"expected_rate":0.995,"n_planned":250,"threshold":0.95}},{"id":"sec-headroom-gate","metric":"/gates/